reviews.review_text:
This is the source! The Missisippi/franklins is truely excellent and is all there - this must be the source that was fixed! What a great combo for an opener!

I love the rest of the show too - great jaming playing.  Pretty good Aud recording to boot!

Reverb Makes All The Dif On This One Right off the bat, you immediately notice ol' Jer butchering Half Step vocally. Yikes! It's a real bummer since I love Half Step sooo much.  But I wasn't going to give up on this baby with HS > Franklin's > Stranger looking totally delish. And it IS boys and girls!  It's just blistering right into Franklin's Tower with a hot Tower!  Barry's typical primo locations and equipment make his audios so scrumptious, I was sure I could do something with it?

This "sweet spot" recording left a lot of room for reverb experimenting to soften Jerry's singing.  I started with a modicum of sustain to see where things would end up and found the crispness and definition of Barry's recording to be so good, I hit the Soundforge board with a heavy dose. And to my surprise, the show held together with not too much boom - and Jerry sounds much, much better.  It's really amazing what you can do to a sweet FOB recording!

The first half of the second set is a scorcher too!  But I desperately wanted to keep the opening. And I'm satisfied with the results.  But be forewarned. The patent pending Garcia Cringe-O-Meter is bouncing around all over the place tonight.
